The White House Press Briefing on March 9, 2011 covered a variety of topics including the nomination of Don Berwick, the situation in Libya, budget talks, Guantanamo Bay, public broadcasting, and the President's meetings with Senate Democratic leaders. Regarding Libya, the briefing emphasized the importance of working with international partners and the need for a coordinated response. There was also discussion about the possibility of implementing a no-fly zone. On the budget, the President's commitment to cutting spending and finding common ground with Republicans was emphasized. The briefing also touched on the issue of public broadcasting and the President's belief in its importance. Finally, there were questions about Guantanamo Bay and the President's commitment to closing the detention facility, as well as the President's approach to domestic radicalization and his outreach to the Muslim community.